response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: Anagram Checker\", \"description\": \"Given two strings `s1` and `s2`, write a function `is_anagram` that determines if `s2` is an anagram of `s1`.\\n\\nAn anagram is a word or phrase formed by rearranging the letters of a different word or phrase, typically using all the original letters exactly once.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef is_anagram(s1: str, s2: str) -> bool:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `s1` (str): A string containing only lowercase English letters.\\n- `s2` (str): Another string containing only lowercase English letters.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns `True` if `s2` is an anagram of `s1`, and `False` otherwise.\", \"code\": \"def is_anagram(s1: str, s2: str) -> bool:\\n    return sorted(s1) == sorted(s2)\", \"tests\": [\"assert is_anagram(\\\"anagram\\\", \\\"nagaram\\\") == True\", \"assert is_anagram(\\\"hello\\\", \\\"world\\\") == False\", \"assert is_anagram(\\\"debitcard\\\", \\\"badcredit\\\") == True\", \"assert is_anagram(\\\"listen\\\", \\\"silent\\\") == True\"] }"
